<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-12T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/319: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-12T17:00:00-04:00">August 12,
                                    1932—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>62. Your 84, August 12, noon. The Department sees no objection to your
                            giving such informal assistance as you may judge advisable in connection
                            with the efforts of American citizens who desire to leave Santos by
                            steamer.</p>
                        <p>It is obvious that if arrangements are made, with the approval of the
                            Brazilian Government, for an American vessel to enter the harbor at
                            Santos, satisfactory assurances will have to be obtained from the
                            insurgents that they will permit the vessel to leave.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>